h1b visa was revoked by my employer.\r\nDevelopments in Feb 2018 :\r\nOn Feb 9th 2018  Capgemini America  offered me a job , and as part of the H1b transfer  i was asked to produce current  pay-slips which i could not as i was not paid . Finally in March 2018 the Capgemini emailed me that they are rolling back the offer citing \" not having status and current pay-slips\". I have the emails.\r\nDevelopments in March 2018:\r\nI left for India on March 15th 2018  to save my status  and to avoid any issues with immigration.\r\nFinally before leaving for India , I complained to Texas Work Force Commission(State) and the Department of Labour(Federal)  . Developments in April 2018:\r\nFinally The  Texas WorkForce Commission  investigator ordered my employer to pay unpaid wages .The employer has deposited  my unpaid wages  to Texas WorkForce Commission  , I am however yet to receive it.\r\nThe Dept of Labour ( Federal ) is yet to assign the case to any official . \r\n\r\nPossible Case of Silent Fraud:\r\nMy employer filed a permanent residency  application but on repeated request  i was not told the file number .The number with which we can identify the case was Masked in email.  Does  this fall under SILENT FRAUD ? I could not know the status of  my file number and hence  the progress of my permanent residency  application . This was done by the employer so that if an employee will come to know that his case status and if its rejected, the will look for another employer.An this is what happened my application was denied and i was not informed about it , nor could i know the status as i had no File number.\r\nThanks and Regards\r\nApurva\r\n+512 905 8213 \r\n\r\n\r\n	\r\nClick here to Reply, Reply to all, or Forward'),(275,98,1,1,'Kelly'),(276,98,1,2,'kellyinternetmarketing4@gmail.com'),(277,99,1,1,'Linda Bailey'),(278,99,1,2,'Linda.Bailey085@gmail.com'),(279,99,1,3,'Hi\r\nWe can help your website to get on first page of Google and increase the number of leads and sales you